In my next.js amplify app, there is a valid policy attached to the Service role.
The role has policy , which has acccess to S3 Read and write.
{
    "Version": "2012-10-17",
    "Statement": [
        {
            "Sid": "DocuFlowSID",
            "Effect": "Allow",
            "Action": [
                "s3:PutObject",
                "s3:GetObject",
                "s3:DeleteObject"
            ],
            "Resource": "arn:aws:s3:::<bucketname>/*"
        }
    ]
}
Even with that, when , I try to put an object on S3, I get ,
Could not load credentials from any providers Error [CredentialsProviderError]: Could not load credentials from any providers

Please try on AWS.config.credentials under Amplify configuration, also check for session expiry
